Part 2.1(c)

In the 1000-transaction data set, the association rules formed from it werent that generalized as they were in the the latter data sets. In the 5000, 20000, and 75000-transaction data sets, we could observe with good lift value how customers tend to buy lemon and raspberry-flavored cookies and lemonade, with green tea. With the emergence of apple-flavored items, we can easily observe that the patterns/rules begin to seem robust/generalizable as more transactions are added in the equation.
